M|rules|title: Promise.all() for Independent Operations
M|rules|impact: CRITICAL
M|rules|impactDescription: 2-10× improvement
M|rules|tags: async, parallelization, promises, waterfalls
M|rules|When async operations have no interdependencies, execute them concurrently using `Promise.all()`.
M|rules|**Incorrect (sequential execution, 3 round trips):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const user = await fetchUser()
M|rules|const posts = await fetchPosts()
M|rules|const comments = await fetchComments()
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (parallel execution, 1 round trip):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const [user, posts, comments] = await Promise.all([
M|rules|fetchUser(),
M|rules|fetchPosts(),
M|rules|fetchComments()
M|rules|])
M|rules|```